channel.title: Server wolnt go online
channel.description:
I have done everything i was supposed to do. I registered with no-ip made a host for my server. downloaded the other DUC thing, used utorrent to portforward, and i have it all running with my server. I clicked log on and it just said it didnt work... Can any one tell me what i am doing wrong?
PS: i have teamviewer

item.title: Server wolnt go online
item.dc:creator: @Mi_K_ey Mi K ey
item.description:
@Mi_K_ey wrote:

1.) Block out your IP you can get warnings because that’s considered [size=36pt]ADVERTISING[/size].
[size=8pt]2.) uTorrent isn’t very Relable with[/size] [size=36pt]PORTFORWARDING[/size], If you have a router try and use that for portforwarding, like for an example on my portforwarding i use Link-sys, And the number that i use to portforward with is [192.168.0] - 103.

Hope this Helps.

Read full topic

item.title: Server wolnt go online
item.dc:creator: @lugmfr lugmfr
item.description:
@lugmfr wrote:

If port 43594 is open and it wont let you login under the no-ip you registered, change it to 0.0.0.0 for YOUR client only. If the port isn’t open try using a static IP if you haven’t done so. If you need more help feel free to PM me.

Read full topic
